**Mounting**

- When the two mounts are completed thread the holes with a 6-32 thread (Not required on newest mount iterations)  
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  


- Secure the AQS Mount onto the top hole with a Grainger \#6 Screw (6-32 x 12'' Phillip Head Screw) with a 6-32 lock nut and a Phillips Bit or 6-32 x 12” Screw with a 6-32 lock nut and a H2.5 Bit. (Make sure that the PCB is screwed into the side with the Lip. So that the PCB will be secure in a vertical position)  
  ![][image2]  
- Insert the Sen5X into the Mount  
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  




- Make sure that the holes line up for the SEX5X Mount and the PCB Board  
  ![][image3]  
- Secure the SEN5X Mount using the hole in the middle of the PCB. 6-32 x 12” Screw with a 6-32 lock nut and a H2.5 Bit or 6-32 x 12'' Phillip Head Screw (This mount should be on the back of the PCB with all the soldered joints)  
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  




- Insert the AQS into a 3in PVC Pipe. (It is a tight fit so try to use moderate pressure. While rotating the AQS for it to be fully placed into the PVC Pipe.)
